<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>SECONDHAND TREASURES</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/news_yardsale_2007-05-10.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<div id='gazette_byline''><em>By Loretta Rivers<br><a href=http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1>Clothing Store</a> owner</em></div>
<b>Thursday, May 10, 2007</b> &mdash; It&#039;s my favorite time of the year! It&#039;s not too hot out and everything&#039;s in bloom. I find myself inspired by all the colors and excitement. <br><br>You might think that since I own a clothing store and design my own clothes I would have no interest in shopping for clothes at yard sales. But I&#039;m out at yard sales every weekend! It&#039;s great for me as a businesswoman, and it&#039;s also great fun. I get to meet people, talk about fashion, find out which clothes are popular, and see how much people are charging so that I can keep my own prices competitive.<br>
<br>
Every Saturday morning, I grab the <i>Gazette</i> and check out the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/classifieds.phtml">Yard Sale Classifieds</a>. I try to mix up the neighborhoods I visit and hope that one day I&#039;ll have walked (and shopped!) every street in Millsberry. <br><br>I pick a neighborhood and then pick a street I haven&#039;t been to before. Then I pick an address that will be my first stop, and hop on my bike. From the first sale, I just walk down the street and see where the day takes me. <br><br>Just recently I was on Thunderbird Place in Ravenwood and saw some amazing deals. Biker boots for 85 Millsbucks! An out-of-season snowflake sweater for 200 Millsbucks! I ended up buying some green star glasses for 38 Millsbucks; another eager shopper rejoiced when she saw the snowflake sweater for such a great price. <br><br>I also encountered some citizens with great style who made me think of some possible designs for fall. One girl on Willow Wood Way wore a bell-shaped skirt with a varsity jacket, both of which she said she purchased in yard sales. I was also delighted to see someone wearing a green wraparound dress. That was so much fun to design! It really brought back memories. And to see her wearing it with legwarmers and flats was also eye-opening. Millsberry citizens are so creative!<br><br>So, I hope you are all enjoying yard sale shopping as much as I am. I love being outdoors. Which reminds me&mdash;come down to the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing Store</a> today and check out the new outdoor clothing for sale. Till then, enjoy the weather and the bargains!</div>
